void VLIB_originalfast12_score ( const uint8_t *restrict  i,

)

Description:
This function computes the FAST12 score for a list of corners, and adds the score to the appropriate field of each feature.
Parameters:
[in] *i Pointer to the image buffer - Must be double-word(64-bit) aligned.
[in] stride The stride of the image.
[in,out] *features The feature list - Must be double-word(64-bit) aligned.
[in] n_features The length of the feature list.
[in] b The FAST difference threshold. A pixel must be this much brighter/darker than the center to be considered "different".
Assumptions:
  • i and features must be double-word(64-bit) aligned.
  • features size should be at least as large as the n_features value.
Implementation Notes:
  • This code is compatible with C6XXX fixed point processors.
Benchmarks:
